    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the two sides but that feels like a bit of an answer for both and neither lol. like if you look at most developed countries they already have it. does that mean the \"inefficient\" argument is basically debunked or is there actually a valid reason why it wouldn't work in places like the us?",
